For this task, I created a Digital Literacy Awareness infographic using Canva. Canva is an easy-to-use online design tool that provides various templates, icons, and design elements, making it suitable for beginners.

My infographic explains the concept of digital literacy and highlights its importance for students. It includes key topics such as useful digital tools like Google Docs and GitHub, safe internet practices like using strong passwords and avoiding suspicious links, and maintaining a professional online presence. I also included basic email etiquette rules to help students communicate effectively in academic and professional settings.

The design is visually appealing with simple icons, headings, and short points to make it easy to understand. I focused on clarity and readability so that anyone can quickly grasp the information.

One interesting thing I found while creating this infographic was how visual elements like icons and colors can make information more engaging. However, selecting the right layout and balancing the content without overcrowding the design was slightly challenging.
